Janet's ducks lay 16 eggs per day. She uses 3 eggs for breakfast and 4 eggs to bake muffins, totaling 7 eggs per day. The remaining eggs sold at the market are:

$$
16 \text{ eggs} - 3 \text{ eggs (breakfast)} - 4 \text{ eggs (muffins)} = 9 \text{ eggs}
$$

Each egg is sold for $2, so the daily revenue is:

$$
9 \text{ eggs} \times \$2/\text{egg} = \$18
$$

**Final Answer:** #### 18
